Introduction

MAMAMOO comprises 4 members: Solar, Moonbyul, Wheein, and Hwasa. MAMAMOO debuted on June 18, 2014, under RBW (formerly WA Entertainment) with the mini album "Hello". Some critics considered their debut as one of the best K-pop debuts of 2014.

Before their official debut, Mamamoo collaborated with several artists. Their first collaboration titled "Don't Be Happy" with Bumkey was released on January 8, 2014. On February 11th, 2014 Mamamoo released their second collaboration with K. Will titled "Peppermint Chocolate" featuring Wheesung. On May 30th Mamamoo released another collaboration with rap duo Geeks called "HeeHeeHaHeHo".

On June 18, 2014, the group made their official debut with the lead single "Mr. Ambiguous" from their first extended play, "Hello". They made their first live appearance on a July ne 19, 2014 episode of Mnet Countdown.
